g value) {\\n            return true;\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public void init(EndpointConfig config) {\\n            INITIALIZED_WITH.set(config);\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public void destroy() {\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    public static class PayloadTextStreamDecoder implements Decoder.TextStream<Payload> {\\n\"}]}\n2359:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating test structure**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether to update or create the `PojoMessageHandlerWholeTextTest`. It seems like the existing `WholeBaseTest` shouldn't exercise it, but currently, it does. The task is to refine tests that are active only. Maybe I can refine the existing `WholeBase` by moving the text test. Is that too broad? I wonder if it's best to migrate the text-decoder test into the new test while leaving `WholeBaseTest` empty. But, can I delete the file?\\n\\n**Inspecting code structure**\\n\\nI’m considering that we might need to maintain one test per dynamic class in the source root. If we don’t, I’m not sure if having two files for the active class will create confusion. Actually, it seems there would be one with active and another existing. I think it would be better to migrate. Let's take a look at the current WholeBase and write a new file expanded with Text and TextStream, then delete the old one. I'll also need to preserve the old PayloadTextDecoder and add a test.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0dd267bb112c9197016a247aa16d688196b0b858dd9945787b\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"content\\\":[],\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABqJHq6NEBQ7dUSZD89x3qiyFxIs09C8ZB4wfqChZCH94oi4jhvUgNNs150w5y9VJB-cDGIHcK8R-61maXymO5I7tqsXBJ5oh_JGFJSYzkLNH7kn6pfn8EvCrUsZE2BP8Z0qhjNwpuP6j-tAnZlLV5MrNdHdTBtOxx_FJnxIwz3CKx_MGhIgjXJdj_rfMD92-vcrTTZoo_hkKe-gnqxRaNwxhrRR0jHlyGf__IGZNrUkZ3xGYJGmPdNQYWSwVPhihN2sqHJ5MAJPI-zP9aRTRpp6OVVK7tPvi5kpwj1ZZGugE